The paper discusses the security of transportation networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of game theory to model the interaction between attackers and defenders suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper proposes heuristic algorithms for finding near-optimal strategies, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of control systems (cs.SY). The use of real-time traffic data and anomaly detection suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the use of Gaussian processes for anomaly detection suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
